d dx psi and p-- yeah.

00:38:43.690 --> 00:38:47.400
They are the same
data, the same state

00:38:47.400 --> 00:38:49.345
represented in different ways.

00:38:49.345 --> 00:38:49.845
Yeah.

00:38:54.800 --> 00:38:55.470
All right.

00:38:55.470 --> 00:38:58.470
So time for a change.

00:38:58.470 --> 00:39:03.460
We're going to talk about
Stern-Gerlach and spin.

00:39:03.460 --> 00:39:09.580
Now, spin will keep us busy the
biggest chunk of this semester.

00:39:09.580 --> 00:39:14.310
So it will be spin-1/2, and
we're really going to go

00:39:14.310 --> 00:39:17.200
into enormous detail on it.

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:20.830
So this is just the
beginning of the story that

00:39:20.830 --> 00:39:25.030
will be elaborated
at various stages.

00:39:25.030 --> 00:39:30.420
So at this moment, I will
talk about this experiment

00:39:30.420 --> 00:39:33.090
that led to the
discovery of spin,

00:39:33.090 --> 00:39:37.200
and if you try to invent
the theory that describes

00:39:37.200 --> 00:39:42.050
this experiment, what you
would possibly begin doing.

00:39:42.050 --> 00:39:44.340
And then we go through
the mathematics,

00:39:44.340 --> 00:39:48.720
as I mentioned to you, for maybe
a week and a half or two weeks,

00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:52.260
and then return to the
spin with more tools

00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:55.960
to understand it well.

00:39:55.960 --> 00:40:00.420
So the subject is the
Stern-Gerlach experiment,

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:06.050
Stern-Gerlach experiment.

00:40:12.650 --> 00:40:21.080
So the Stern-Gerlach experiment
was done in Frankfurt, 1922.

00:40:21.080 --> 00:40:23.930
It was an experiment
that, in fact, people

00:40:23.930 --> 00:40:25.672
were extraordinarily confused.

00:40:25.672 --> 00:40:29.080
It was not clear why
they were doing it.

00:40:29.080 --> 00:40:33.590
And for quite a
while, people didn't

00:40:33.590 --> 00:40:37.170
understand what
they were getting,

00:40:37.170 --> 00:40:39.400
what was happening with it.

00:40:39.400 --> 00:40:46.760
In fact, Pauli had thought
that the electron has

00:40:46.760 --> 00:40:48.890
like two degrees of
freedom and didn't

00:40:48.890 --> 00:40:53.410
know what it was, those
two degrees of freedom.

00:40:53.410 --> 00:40:57.605
Kronig suggested that
it had to do somehow

00:40:57.605 --> 00:41:01.350
with the rotation
of the electron.

00:41:01.350 --> 00:41:05.620
Now, Pauli said that's nonsense.

00:41:05.620 --> 00:41:09.950
How can an electron rotate
and have angular momentum

00:41:09.950 --> 00:41:11.770
because it has a rotation?

00:41:11.770 --> 00:41:15.450
It would have to rotate
so fast, even faster

00:41:15.450 --> 00:41:18.200
than the speed of light to
have the angular momentum,

00:41:18.200 --> 00:41:21.510
and then this little ball
that would be the electron

00:41:21.510 --> 00:41:22.790
would disintegrate.

00:41:22.790 --> 00:41:27.060
And it made no sense to him that
there would be such a thing.

00:41:27.060 --> 00:41:30.890
So Kronig didn't publish this.

00:41:30.890 --> 00:41:35.986
Then there were another two
people, Uhlenbeck and Goudsmit,

00:41:35.986 --> 00:41:40.190
at the same time,
around 1925, had

00:41:40.190 --> 00:41:44.870
the same idea, angular
momentum of this particle.

00:41:44.870 --> 00:41:48.860
And their advisor was
Ehrenfest, and said

00:41:48.860 --> 00:41:52.285
it doesn't make too much sense,
but you should publish it.

00:41:52.285 --> 00:41:54.390
[LAUGHTER]

00:41:54.390 --> 00:41:57.080
And thanks to their
publishing, they

00:41:57.080 --> 00:42:00.430
are given credit for discovering
the spin of the electron.

00:42:00.430 --> 00:42:03.390
And Pauli, a couple
of years later,

00:42:03.390 --> 00:42:05.260
decided, after all, I was wrong.

00:42:05.260 --> 00:42:08.380
Yes, it is spin, and
it's all working out.

00:42:08.380 --> 00:42:14.160
And 1927, five years after
the experiment basically,

00:42:14.160 --> 00:42:17.110
people understood
what was going on.

00:42:17.110 --> 00:42:20.040
So what were these
people trying to do?

00:42:20.040 --> 00:42:23.400
First, Stern and Gerlach
were atomic physicists,

00:42:23.400 --> 00:42:26.550
and they were just
interested in measuring

00:42:26.550 --> 00:42:34.220
speeds of thermal
motion of ions.

00:42:34.220 --> 00:42:37.460
So they would send
beams of these ions

00:42:37.460 --> 00:42:41.530
and put magnetic fields and
deflect them and measure

00:42:41.530 --> 00:42:43.550
their velocities.

00:42:43.550 --> 00:42:46.170
And eventually,
they were experts

00:42:46.170 --> 00:42:47.580
doing this kind of thing.

00:42:47.580 --> 00:42:51.630
And they heard of Bohr, that
said that the electron has

00:42:51.630 --> 00:42:56.440
angular momentum and is going
around the proton in circles,

00:42:56.440 --> 00:42:58.280
so it might have
angular momentum.

00:42:58.280 --> 00:43:01.120
They said, oh, if it has
angular momentum because it's

00:43:01.120 --> 00:43:05.330
going around the proton,
maybe we can detect it.

00:43:05.330 --> 00:43:09.080
And when they did the
experiment, they got something.

00:43:09.080 --> 00:43:11.510
And they said, well,
we're seeing it.

00:43:11.510 --> 00:43:14.520
But it was not that.

00:43:14.520 --> 00:43:17.700
They were not seeing the
orbital angular momentum

00:43:17.700 --> 00:43:24.650
of the electron because that
electron in these silver atoms

00:43:24.650 --> 00:43:27.310
actually has no
angular momentum,

00:43:27.310 --> 00:43:30.340
as we will see, no
orbital angular momentum.

00:43:30.340 --> 00:43:31.370
It only has spin.

00:43:31.370 --> 00:43:34.220
So they were actually
seeing the spin.

00:43:34.220 --> 00:43:36.090
So it was a big confusion.

00:43:36.090 --> 00:43:37.650
It took some time.

00:43:37.650 --> 00:43:41.660
Basically, they took the
beam, and they split it

00:43:41.660 --> 00:43:45.770
with a magnetic field,
and the clean split

00:43:45.770 --> 00:43:47.510
was something nobody understood.

00:43:47.510 --> 00:43:51.440
So they called it
space quantization,

00:43:51.440 --> 00:43:54.500
as of it's separated in space.

00:43:54.500 --> 00:43:56.710
Space is quantized.

00:43:56.710 --> 00:43:59.570
A pretty awful name, of course.

00:43:59.570 --> 00:44:03.200
There's nothing quantized
about space here.

00:44:03.200 --> 00:44:07.600
But it reflects that when
you don't know what's really

00:44:07.600 --> 00:44:12.500
happening, your names
don't come out too well.

00:44:12.500 --> 00:44:17.460
So what we have to
understand here,

00:44:17.460 --> 00:44:20.540
our goal today is
to just see what's

00:44:20.540 --> 00:44:27.310
happening in that experiment,
quantify a bit the results,

00:44:27.310 --> 00:44:33.050
and then extract the quantum
mechanical lessons from it.

00:44:33.050 --> 00:44:35.900
So let us begin with
the important thing.

00:44:35.900 --> 00:44:39.380
You don't see the spin directly.

00:44:39.380 --> 00:44:43.930
What you see is
magnetic moments.

00:44:43.930 --> 00:44:45.600
So what's that?

00:44:45.600 --> 00:44:47.680
So what are magnetic moments?

00:44:47.680 --> 00:45:00.340
Magnetic moments, mu, is the
analog, the magnetic analog

00:45:00.340 --> 00:45:01.780
of an electric dipole.

00:45:01.780 --> 00:45:03.740
A mu is called a
magnetic dipole.

00:45:03.740 --> 00:45:05.740
You say it has a
magnetic moment.

00:45:08.680 --> 00:45:14.160
And the magnetic moment is
given by I times the area.

00:45:14.160 --> 00:45:15.490
What does that mean?

00:45:15.490 --> 00:45:20.360
Well, a precise discussion
would take some time.

00:45:20.360 --> 00:45:24.110
But roughly, you
can simplify when

00:45:24.110 --> 00:45:28.150
you think of a loop that is
in a plane, in which case

00:45:28.150 --> 00:45:31.270
there's an area
associated to it.

00:45:31.270 --> 00:45:33.570
And if the loop is
this one, the area

00:45:33.570 --> 00:45:38.280
is defined as the normal
vector to the oriented loop.

00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:42.140
So an oriented loop
has an area vector.

00:45:42.140 --> 00:45:43.960
And the orientation
could be focused

00:45:43.960 --> 00:45:45.500
the direction of the current.

00:45:45.500 --> 00:45:46.450
There is some area.

00:45:46.450 --> 00:45:49.970
And the magnetic moment
is given by this thing.

00:45:49.970 --> 00:45:52.520
It points up in
the circumstances

00:45:52.520 --> 00:45:55.580
when this current
goes like that.

00:45:55.580 --> 00:45:58.630
So that's a magnetic moment.

00:45:58.630 --> 00:46:01.930
A little bit of units.

00:46:01.930 --> 00:46:06.020
The way units work out is
that mu B-- magnetic moments

00:46:06.020 --> 00:46:11.190
and magnetic fields
have units of energy.

00:46:14.680 --> 00:46:19.140
So magnetic moments
you could define

00:46:19.140 --> 00:46:26.450
as energy, which is
joules, divided by tesla,

00:46:26.450 --> 00:46:32.520
or ergs divided by
gauss, because mu B has

00:46:32.520 --> 00:46:35.490
units of energy.

00:46:35.490 --> 00:46:39.300
So how do magnetic
moments originate

00:46:39.300 --> 00:46:43.340
in a charge configuration?

00:46:43.340 --> 00:46:46.230
Well, you can simply have
a little current like that.

00:46:46.230 --> 00:46:49.630
But let's consider a
different situation

00:46:49.630 --> 00:46:58.040
in which you have
a ring of charge,

00:46:58.040 --> 00:47:08.945
a ring of charge of some radius
R. It has a total charge Q,

00:47:08.945 --> 00:47:12.350
and it has a linear
charge density lambda.

00:47:12.350 --> 00:47:17.980
It's uniform, and it's
rotating with some velocity

00:47:17.980 --> 00:47:24.220
v. If you wish, it also
has a mass M. There are all

00:47:24.220 --> 00:47:25.720
kinds of [? parameters. ?]
How many?

00:47:25.720 --> 00:47:29.490
Mass, charge,
radius, and velocity.

00:47:29.490 --> 00:47:30.100
Here we go.

00:47:30.100 --> 00:47:35.250
We have our solid ring
of charge rotating,

00:47:35.250 --> 00:47:39.030
and we want to figure out
something quite fundamental,

00:47:39.030 --> 00:47:41.470
which is the origin
of this principle.

00:47:41.470 --> 00:47:46.300
We said, you really
never see spins directly.

00:47:46.300 --> 00:47:49.960
You never see this intrinsic
angular momentum directly.

00:47:49.960 --> 00:47:53.280
You see magnetic moments.

00:47:53.280 --> 00:47:55.800
But then actually
what happens is

00:47:55.800 --> 00:47:58.310
that there's a
universal relation

00:47:58.310 --> 00:48:00.615
between magnetic moments
and angular momentum.

00:48:00.615 --> 00:48:04.370
This is a key
concept in physics.

00:48:04.370 --> 00:48:05.890
Maybe you've seen it before.

00:48:05.890 --> 00:48:07.080
Maybe you haven't.

00:48:07.080 --> 00:48:11.540
Probably you might
have seen that in 802.

00:48:11.540 --> 00:48:13.040
So how does that go?

00:48:13.040 --> 00:48:16.020
Let's calculate the
magnetic moment.

00:48:16.020 --> 00:48:22.830
So the current is the
linear charge density

00:48:22.830 --> 00:48:23.650
times the velocity.

00:48:28.440 --> 00:48:32.760
The linear charge density
is the total charge

00:48:32.760 --> 00:48:35.705
divided by 2 pi R
times the velocity.

00:48:38.360 --> 00:48:41.060
Now the area, to give
the magnetic moment,

00:48:41.060 --> 00:48:44.120
we'll have mu is equal
to I times the area.

00:48:44.120 --> 00:48:49.300
So it would be this
Q times 2 pi R v

00:48:49.300 --> 00:48:54.700
times the area, which
would be pi R squared.

00:48:54.700 --> 00:49:00.605
So the pi's cancel,
and we get 1/2 QvR.

00:49:08.520 --> 00:49:10.550
OK.

00:49:10.550 --> 00:49:14.510
1/2 QvR, and that's
fine and interesting.

00:49:14.510 --> 00:49:20.230
But OK, depends on the radius,
depends on the velocity.

00:49:20.230 --> 00:49:26.200
So here is the magnetic moment
is supposed to be going up.

00:49:26.200 --> 00:49:27.730
But what else is going up?

00:49:27.730 --> 00:49:31.020
The angular momentum of
this thing is also going up.

00:49:31.020 --> 00:49:35.026
So what is the magnitude
of the angular momentum L?

00:49:35.026 --> 00:49:36.476
L is angular momentum.

00:49:39.700 --> 00:49:43.690
Well, it's the mass
times the momentum--

00:49:43.690 --> 00:49:47.970
it's the mass momentum
cross R, so MvR.

00:49:53.790 --> 00:49:58.270
The momentum of R
cross p for each piece,

00:49:58.270 --> 00:50:02.910
contributes the same, so you
just take the total momentum.

00:50:02.910 --> 00:50:06.260
This really is 0, but add
them up little by little,

00:50:06.260 --> 00:50:08.270
and you've got your MvR.

00:50:11.050 --> 00:50:22.780
So here you have vR, so here
you put 1/2 Q over M MvR.

00:50:25.330 --> 00:50:38.600
And you discover that mu
is equal to 1/2 Q over M L.

00:50:38.600 --> 00:50:49.430
So maybe write it better--
Q over 2M L. I'm sorry,

00:50:49.430 --> 00:50:50.835
this is the normal.

00:50:50.835 --> 00:50:54.710
The M shouldn't change, M.

00:50:54.710 --> 00:50:59.680
And I box this relation
because an interesting thing

00:50:59.680 --> 00:51:00.440
has happened.

00:51:00.440 --> 00:51:04.510
All kinds of incidentals
have dropped out.

00:51:04.510 --> 00:51:08.090
Like the velocity
has dropped out.

00:51:08.090 --> 00:51:11.140
The radius has
dropped out as well.

00:51:11.140 --> 00:51:14.140
So if I have one
ring with this radius

00:51:14.140 --> 00:51:16.390
and another ring
with a bigger radius,

00:51:16.390 --> 00:51:19.740
the relation between
mu and L is the same,

00:51:19.740 --> 00:51:23.090
as long as it's rotating
with the same speed.

00:51:23.090 --> 00:51:26.900
So this is actually
a universal relation.

00:51:26.900 --> 00:51:29.330
It is not just true
for a little ring.

00:51:29.330 --> 00:51:33.790
It's true for a solid sphere
or any solid object axially

00:51:33.790 --> 00:51:35.880
symmetric.

00:51:35.880 --> 00:51:36.830
It would be true.

00:51:36.830 --> 00:51:43.030
You could consider any object
that is axially symmetric,

00:51:43.030 --> 00:51:45.870
and then you start considering
all the little rings that

00:51:45.870 --> 00:51:46.710
can be built.

00:51:46.710 --> 00:51:49.340
And for every ring,
mu over L is the same,

00:51:49.340 --> 00:51:51.880
and they all point in
the same direction.

00:51:51.880 --> 00:51:56.220
Therefore, it's true under
very general grounds.

00:51:56.220 --> 00:51:59.790
And that is a very
famous relation.

00:51:59.790 --> 00:52:03.770
So now you could
speculate that, indeed,

00:52:03.770 --> 00:52:12.390
the reason that a particle may
have a magnetic moment if it's

00:52:12.390 --> 00:52:15.610
made by a little ball of
charge that is rotating.

00:52:15.610 --> 00:52:18.900
But that was exactly what
Pauli didn't like, of course.

00:52:21.928 --> 00:52:24.600
And you would like
to see what's really

00:52:24.600 --> 00:52:25.980
happening with particles.

00:52:25.980 --> 00:52:31.770
So when you think of a true
quantum mechanical particle,

00:52:31.770 --> 00:52:37.550
let's think of a particle
in general, a solid particle

00:52:37.550 --> 00:52:38.110
rotating.

00:52:38.110 --> 00:52:43.160
We'll change the name to S
for spin angular momentum.

00:52:43.160 --> 00:52:46.480
Because that little part,
this is just one particle.

00:52:46.480 --> 00:52:48.920
We're not thinking of
that little particle

00:52:48.920 --> 00:52:51.700
going around a nucleus.

00:52:51.700 --> 00:52:55.310
We're thinking of that
little particle rotating.

00:52:55.310 --> 00:52:57.620
So this is a little piece
of that little particle

00:52:57.620 --> 00:52:59.270
that is rotating.

00:52:59.270 --> 00:53:08.640
So you could ask,
if, for the electron,

00:53:08.640 --> 00:53:12.150
for example, is
it true that mu is

00:53:12.150 --> 00:53:17.595
equal to e over 2 mass of
the electron times its spin?

00:53:22.030 --> 00:53:28.040
So this would be a vindication
of this classical analysis.

00:53:28.040 --> 00:53:34.770
It might be that it's
related in this way.

00:53:34.770 --> 00:53:48.910
So actually, it's
not quite true,

00:53:48.910 --> 00:53:53.080
but let's still improve
this a little bit.

00:53:53.080 --> 00:54:00.590
In terms of units, we like to
put an h bar here and a 2Me.

00:54:00.590 --> 00:54:05.700
And put spin here, angular
momentum, divided by h.

00:54:05.700 --> 00:54:11.960
Because this has no
units, h bar has the units

00:54:11.960 --> 00:54:17.000
of angular momentum, x times p.

00:54:17.000 --> 00:54:19.390
It's the same units, so
units of angular momentum.

00:54:19.390 --> 00:54:24.430
So h bar would be convenient.

00:54:24.430 --> 00:54:33.270
So that over here, you would
have units of a dipole moment,

00:54:33.270 --> 00:54:38.300
or magnetic moment,
magnetic moment units.

00:54:43.300 --> 00:54:47.810
So what does happen
for the electron?

00:54:47.810 --> 00:54:52.810
Well, it's almost
true, but not quite.

00:54:52.810 --> 00:54:57.680
In fact, what you get is
that you need a fudge factor.

00:54:57.680 --> 00:55:00.700
The fudge factor
is that, actually,

00:55:00.700 --> 00:55:02.800
for elementary
particles, you have

00:55:02.800 --> 00:55:06.980
a g, which is a constant,
which is the fudge factor,

00:55:06.980 --> 00:55:15.850
e h bar 2 over M of the
particle S over h bar.

00:55:15.850 --> 00:55:19.410
Sometimes called
the Lande factor.

00:55:19.410 --> 00:55:22.410
You must put a number there.

00:55:22.410 --> 00:55:28.140
Now, the good thing is
that the number sometimes

00:55:28.140 --> 00:55:31.030
can be calculated and predicted.

00:55:31.030 --> 00:55:34.100
So when people did
this, they figured out

00:55:34.100 --> 00:55:38.950
that for the electron the
number is actually a 2.

00:55:38.950 --> 00:55:46.210
So for the electron, g of
the electron is equal to 2.

00:55:46.210 --> 00:55:49.770
Now that, you would say,
cannot be an accident.

00:55:49.770 --> 00:55:54.720
It's twice what you would
predict sort of classically.

00:55:54.720 --> 00:55:59.250
And the Dirac equation,
the relativistic equation

00:55:59.250 --> 00:56:02.010
of the electron that
you have not studied yet

00:56:02.010 --> 00:56:07.200
but you will study soon,
predicts this g equal to 2.

00:56:07.200 --> 00:56:08.880
It was considered
a great success

00:56:08.880 --> 00:56:12.670
that that equation gave the
right answer, that people

00:56:12.670 --> 00:56:16.400
understood that this
number was going to be 2.

00:56:16.400 --> 00:56:19.670
So for the electron, this is 2.

00:56:19.670 --> 00:56:25.210
So this quantity is called--
it's a magnetic dipole

00:56:25.210 --> 00:56:32.210
moment-- is called mu
B for Bohr magneton.

00:56:39.900 --> 00:56:44.330
So how big is a mu B?

00:56:44.330 --> 00:56:51.880
It's about 9.3 times 10 to
the minus 24 joules per tesla.

00:56:55.454 --> 00:56:56.380
AUDIENCE: Professor.

00:56:56.380 --> 00:56:57.520
PROFESSOR: Yes?

00:56:57.520 --> 00:56:58.966
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:56:58.966 --> 00:57:01.376
So where exactly does
the fudge factor come in?

00:57:01.376 --> 00:57:05.112
Is it just merely
because [INAUDIBLE]?

00:57:05.112 --> 00:57:05.820
PROFESSOR: Right.

00:57:05.820 --> 00:57:11.590
So the classical
analysis is not valid.

00:57:11.590 --> 00:57:14.800
So it's pretty invalid, in fact.

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:19.530
You see, the picture
of an electron,

00:57:19.530 --> 00:57:22.480
as of today, is that
it's a point particle.

00:57:22.480 --> 00:57:27.200
And a point particle
literally means no size.

00:57:27.200 --> 00:57:30.880
The electron is not a
little ball of charge.

00:57:30.880 --> 00:57:32.740
Otherwise, it would have parts.

00:57:32.740 --> 00:57:34.970
So an electron is
a point particle.

00:57:34.970 --> 00:57:38.250
Therefore, a point particle
cannot be rotating and have

00:57:38.250 --> 00:57:39.020
a spin.

00:57:39.020 --> 00:57:43.670
So how does the electron
manage to have spin?

00:57:43.670 --> 00:57:45.720
That you can't
answer in physics.

00:57:45.720 --> 00:57:47.590
It just has it.

00:57:47.590 --> 00:57:51.640
Just like a point particle
that has no size can have mass.

00:57:51.640 --> 00:57:54.670
How do you have mass
if you have no size?

00:57:54.670 --> 00:57:56.130
You get accustomed to the idea.

00:57:56.130 --> 00:57:58.550
The mathematics
says it's possible.

00:57:58.550 --> 00:58:00.420
You don't run into trouble.

00:58:00.420 --> 00:58:06.510
So this particle has no size,
but it has an angular spin,

00:58:06.510 --> 00:58:09.070
angular momentum, as if
it would be rotating.

00:58:09.070 --> 00:58:12.520
But it's definitely not the
case that it's rotating.

00:58:12.520 --> 00:58:17.420
And therefore, this 2 confirms
that it was a pointless idea

00:58:17.420 --> 00:58:19.260
to believe that
it would be true.

00:58:19.260 --> 00:58:22.720
Nevertheless, kind
of unit analyses

00:58:22.720 --> 00:58:26.770
or maybe some truth to the
fact that quantum mechanics

00:58:26.770 --> 00:58:29.290
changes classical mechanics.

00:58:29.290 --> 00:58:32.580
Turns out that it's
closely related.

00:58:32.580 --> 00:58:36.910
For the proton, for example, the
magnetic moment of the proton

00:58:36.910 --> 00:58:40.510
is quite complicated as well
because the proton is made out

00:58:40.510 --> 00:58:43.110
of quarks that are
rotating inside.

00:58:43.110 --> 00:58:47.070
And how do you get
the spin of the proton

00:58:47.070 --> 00:58:48.790
and the magnetic
moment of the proton?

00:58:48.790 --> 00:58:50.000
It's complicated.

00:58:50.000 --> 00:58:54.560
The neutron, that has no
charge, has a magnetic moment,

00:58:54.560 --> 00:58:58.450
because somehow the quarks
inside arrange in a way

00:58:58.450 --> 00:59:01.900
that their angular momentum
doesn't quite cancel.

00:59:05.580 --> 00:59:08.690
So for example, the value
for a neutron, I believe,

00:59:08.690 --> 00:59:12.390
is minus 2.78 or
something like that.

00:59:12.390 --> 00:59:14.770
It's a strange number.

00:59:14.770 --> 00:59:19.070
Another thing that is sort of
interesting that is also true

00:59:19.070 --> 00:59:22.390
is that this mass is
the mass of a particle.

00:59:22.390 --> 00:59:25.250
So if you're talking
about the magnetic moment

00:59:25.250 --> 00:59:28.530
of the proton or
the neutron, it's

00:59:28.530 --> 00:59:31.740
suppressed with respect to
the one of the electron.

00:59:31.740 --> 00:59:34.580
The electron one is much bigger
because, actually, the mass

00:59:34.580 --> 00:59:36.440
shows up here.

00:59:36.440 --> 00:59:40.860
So for a neutron or a
proton, the magnetic moment

00:59:40.860 --> 00:59:44.210
is much, much smaller.

00:59:44.210 --> 00:59:48.560
So, in fact, for an
electron then, you

00:59:48.560 --> 00:59:49.870
would have the following.

00:59:49.870 --> 01:00:01.720
Mu is equal to minus g, which
is 2, mu B S bar over h.

01:00:01.720 --> 01:00:04.280
And actually, we
put the minus sign

01:00:04.280 --> 01:00:07.820
because the electron
has negative charge.

01:00:07.820 --> 01:00:12.270
So the magnetic moment
actually points opposite.

01:00:12.270 --> 01:00:16.120
If you rotate this way, the
angular momentum is always up.

01:00:16.120 --> 01:00:18.770
But if you rotate this
way and you're negative,

01:00:18.770 --> 01:00:21.740
it's as if the current goes
in the other direction.

01:00:21.740 --> 01:00:25.871
So this is due to the fact
that the electron is negatively

01:00:25.871 --> 01:00:26.370
charged.

01:00:26.370 --> 01:00:28.870
And that's the final expression.

01:00:31.740 --> 01:00:38.765
So OK, so that's the general
story with magnetic moments.

01:00:42.390 --> 01:00:45.360
So the next thing is,
how do magnetic moments

01:00:45.360 --> 01:00:49.530
react when you have
magnetic fields?

01:00:49.530 --> 01:00:54.710
So that is something
that you can calculate,

01:00:54.710 --> 01:00:57.790
or you can decide if
you have a picture.

01:00:57.790 --> 01:01:03.650
For example, if you have a
loop of charge like this,

01:01:03.650 --> 01:01:10.050
and you have magnetic field
lines that go like this,

01:01:10.050 --> 01:01:11.795
they diverge a bit.

01:01:15.830 --> 01:01:18.220
Let me see you use
your right-hand rule

01:01:18.220 --> 01:01:20.950
and tell me whether
that loop of current

01:01:20.950 --> 01:01:22.925
